# persist
## 1.1: continue to exist; endure

  *  The stories of alien abduction persist despite a decided lack of evidence.
  *  The smell persisted long after we had removed curtains.
  *  Violence persists in Gaza.

## 1.2: continue doing something with no intention of stopping

  *  She persisted to call me every night.
  *  He persists in promoting lies about immigrant leprosy cases.
  *  You must persist if you ever want to become a published writer!
